                <p>Physical device security involves protecting your smart home devices from physical tampering, theft, or damage. Place devices in secure locations where they're not easily accessible to unauthorized individuals, and consider using security screws or other physical protection measures for critical devices. Regularly inspect devices for signs of tampering or damage.</p>
                
