                <p>Data minimization and collection limits can help reduce privacy risks by limiting the amount of data collected and stored by smart home devices. Users should review device privacy settings, disable unnecessary data collection, and understand what data is being collected and how it's used. This minimization can help reduce privacy risks and protect sensitive information.</p>
                
